30/03/2008
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The UN war crimes tribunal in The Hague will announce its verdict against former Kosovo Prime Minister Ramush Haradinaj on Thursday (April 3rd), according to a statement Friday. Haradinaj -- a former regional commander of the Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA) -- and two other KLA members are charged with murder, rape, torture and other crimes against Serb civilians and ethnic Albanian collaborators during the 1998-1999 conflict. Prosecutors seek 25-year prison terms for each defendant, all of whom have pleaded not guilty. (Reuters- 28/03/08)
